<block>
    <para>
        Shows how to use &REK; with the &JSBlong; to create an app that uses &REK; to identify objects by category in images
        located in an &S3long; (&S3;) bucket. The app sends the admin an email notification with the results using
        &SESlong; (&SES;).
    </para>
    <para>Learn how to:</para>
    <itemizedlist>
        <listitem><para>Create an unauthenticated user using &COG;.</para></listitem>
        <listitem><para>Analyze images for objects using &REK;.</para></listitem>
        <listitem><para>Verify an email address for &SES;.</para></listitem>
        <listitem><para>Send an email notification using &SES;.</para></listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
    <para>
        For complete source code and instructions on how to set up and run, see the full example on
        <ulink url="https://github.com/awsdocs/aws-doc-sdk-examples/tree/main/javascriptv3/example_code/cross-services/photo_analyzer">GitHub</ulink>.
    </para>
</block>
